🌌 Space Fact of the Day

A **single teaspoon of neutron‑star material would weigh about a billion tons on Earth**. ⭐

Neutron stars form when massive stars explode in a supernova and collapse into extremely dense objects. Their gravity compresses matter so tightly that **protons and electrons combine into neutrons**, creating one of the densest forms of matter known in the universe.

