### 🌌 Space Fact of the Day

**Venus has a day longer than its year.**

* One full rotation on Venus takes **243 Earth days**.
* But Venus completes one orbit around the Sun in **about 225 Earth days**.

So a **single Venusian day lasts longer than a Venusian year**, mainly because the planet rotates extremely slowly and in the opposite direction of most planets.

